### Example .env for the Database Travel project
### Copy this file to `.env` and fill in values for your local machine:

# Path to SQLite database file (relative to project root)
# If you want data in a subfolder, e.g. ./data/travel_app.db, make sure the folder exists.
DB_PATH=./travel_app.template.db

# Server port
PORT=3000

# Notes:
# - Do not commit your real `.env` to the repository. Add `.env` to .gitignore.
# - Use environment variables in production (e.g., set PORT or DB path via Docker/host).

# (Optional) Frontend origin to allow via CORS. Example: http://localhost:5173
# If you don't set this, the server allows all origins (development only).
CORS_ORIGIN=*

# Optional external Python chat API endpoint
CHAT_API_URL=
